This place certainly surprised me.
While their selection isn't as vast as other buffets, it felt like the quality of cooked food was better and not as oily.
They even had one of my favorite dishes, the "fish fragrant eggplant" (direct translation)!
I've tried a lot of different chinese restaurants and buffets, and this is probably the best I've had in AZ.
Another thing that surprised me was how fresh and sweet the fruits were...it certainly tastes a lot better than the fruits I normally get at Costco!
We went around 7 pm and the place probably had no more than 20 customers.
Service was good, drinks were filled consistently, and the staff even apologized that some food wasn't as fresh due to lack of customers.
When they ran out of the eggplant dish we requested some more, and within ten minutes a fresh batch was put out!
I think it'll be just a matter of time before more people discover this place.
I have already become a regular!
