Yay, a new Buffet!
This lovely new place that occupies the former home of Panda Buffet, which closed a while back, rang all of my bells when I dropped in to try it for lunch today, joined by Arlin B.
& Mike C.  From the awesome Hot & Sour Soup to the tasty & somewhat different Sushi to the big selection of 132 food items overall, plus sauces & dressings, this place is a winner!
There were tasty ribs, various kinds of fish & other seafood, lots of chicken dishes (of course), & interesting veggies.
Yes, they have a nice Mongolian BBQ too, along with EIGHT kinds of good, real ice cream kept at the right temperature, & numerous other desserts.
The service from "LInda" was excellent too.
:-))

I'm that guy who likes both white table linen restaurants, and Asian buffets.
My usual spot is closed so I use the Yelp app to see what else is within 10 miles and I am pointed to Oriental Buffet.
It's hard to find even with GPS.
The vast expanse of far North Peoria at night is a ghost town with little pockets of colorfully-lighted civilization along Lake Pleasant Pkwy.
Here, next to a Wal-Mart, illuminated by the same fluorescent lighting you'd find in a government office building, is a very decent Asian dining find.
Their sushi selection is not the most expansive, but it's serviceable.
It's the cooked seafood on the steam tables that is really, really good.
The ginger fried shrimp and the crab (not the Snow Crab legs, which cost extra $$) are awesome.
You should eat the head-on shrimp with the shell after removing the legs.
The head is edible, but kinda pokey for the mouth, so chew gently.
Crunchy and damn good.
The cut up clusters of lump crabmeat and legs are also completely edible, shell and all, however, you'll find the claws and the joints tougher to masticate so no one would blame you for picking out the meat and discarding those parts.
Steamed clams, and mussels and shrimp prepared in other ways are also available, and so are a few different preparations of fish, but it's the crabs and shrimp that really stand out and what I'll come back for.

Food and service are great.
However the lighting in the restaurant is very bright and destroys the ambiance.

